stine and The Misery of Philosophy—is traced in different and often conflicting manners, which bring out the different currents that traverse his writings and the sites of tension that such terms as "different," "affect," and "infancy" mark. What emerges is not a grand narrative that would organize Lyotard's life and work around one unifying idea, but multifaceted approaches that extend in new and unforeseen directions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Deconstruction.2bisacsh1 aBennington, Geoffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonnefis, Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDerrida, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFynsk, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGasché, Rodolphe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlowacka, Dorota, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNaas, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNouvet, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNouvet, Claire, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPlonowska Ziarek, Ewa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRonell, Avital, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSfez, Gérald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStahuljak, Zrinka, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStill, Kent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStill, Kent, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362509940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/97815